  <description>
    <p>
      This DHCP server program will assign IP addresses ten seconds after it received packets from clients. So it can be used in networks that already have a dhcp server running. For most (WIFI) networks, it will just show what is happening and not interfere.
    </p>
    <p>
      This Python DHCP server
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>shows clients in the network</li>
      <li>lists IP address, Mac address and host name</li>
      <li>highlights recently refreshed/added clients</li>
      <li>assigns IP addresses 10 seconds later than usual DHCP servers</li>
      <li>remembers addresses in the hosts.csv file.</li>
      <li>can be configured to serve all DHCP options using Python</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Contributions welcome!
    </p>
    <p>
      Installation and running need to be done as root because the DHCP port
      can not be accessed as a normal user:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>sudo flatpak install io.github.niccokunzmann.python_dhcp_server</li>
      <li>sudo -i flatpak run io.github.niccokunzmann.python_dhcp_server</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      If you wish, you can edit the .desktop file, so you can run the program as root.
    </p>
  </description>

